# Arcuris — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Arcuris is a Next.js web app that helps new grad job seekers generate tailored resumes and track job applications. It archives the user's full experience inventory, then curates it to match each job description using AI.

---

## Tech Stack
- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- **Auth + Database:** Supabase
- **AI:** Google Gemini API
- **Hosting:** Vercel

---

## UI Components — shadcn/ui First

Always use shadcn/ui components before writing any custom UI. Never write raw HTML inputs, buttons, cards, dialogs, or form elements when a shadcn equivalent exists.

**Import pattern:**
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input"
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"
```

If a needed component is not in the installed, run `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` rather than building a custom version.

