## Next.js App Router Rules

- Default to **Server Components**. Only add `"use client"` when the component needs interactivity, browser APIs, or React hooks.
- Data fetching happens in Server Components or API routes — never fetch Gemini or Supabase directly inside a Client Component.
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` in each route folder.
- Use Next.js `redirect()` from `next/navigation` for server-side redirects.
- Use `useRouter()` from `next/navigation` for client-side navigation — never `next/router`.

---

## Supabase Rules

**Two clients — use the right one:**

Server-side (API routes, Server Components):
```ts
import { createServerClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server"
```

Client-side (Client Components):
```ts
import { createBrowserClient } from "@/lib/supabase/client"
```

- Never use the service role key in client components
- Always scope queries with `eq("user_id", user.id)` — RLS is enabled but defense in depth matters
- Use typed Supabase queries with the generated Database types from `/lib/types/supabase.ts`

---

## Gemini API Rules

- **Never call the Gemini API from a client component.** All Gemini calls go through Next.js API routes in `/app/api/`.
- The Gemini API key is `GEMINI_API_KEY` — only accessible server-side via `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY`.
- All prompts are defined in `/lib/prompts` — never hardcode prompt strings inline in API routes.
- Always handle Gemini errors gracefully and return a meaningful error message to the client.

**Standard API route pattern:**
```ts
import { GoogleGenerativeAI } from "@google/generative-ai"

const genAI = new GoogleGenerativeAI(process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY!)
const model = genAI.getGenerativeModel({ model: "gemini-1.5-pro" })
```

---

## Environment Variables

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=        ← server-side only, never expose to client
GEMINI_API_KEY=                   ← server-side only, never expose to client
```

Never reference `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` or `GEMINI_API_KEY` in any file with `"use client"` or in any component passed to the client bundle.

